Production tolerances as low as 1% can create a variance of 25% in lamp life, so in general some lamps will fail well before the rated life expectancy, and some will last much longer.
For LEDs, lamp life is defined as the operation time at which 50% of lamps have experienced a 70% decrease in light output.
